Male. Eighth abdominal tergite only little prolonged. Ninth abdominal tergite globular with apical margin roundly excised in middle; on both sides of excision with a long narrow down-curved hook. Tenth abdominal tergite with a pair of upcurved hooks touching each other in middle; in apical view hooks elongate, conical, with dark brown acute apical area; in lateral view compressed, nearly rectangularly upcurved with distal margin running straight into darkened apical area, while proximal margin curved ( Figs. 56 A–B). Subgenital plate almost as long as wide; apical margin with two triangular lobes (little shorter than in
D. orlovi
), concave at both sides; styli stout, slightly upcurved and in apical area conical ( Fig. 56C ). Phallus with a narrow elongate but little sinuate sclerite with forked and recurved base, in situ embedded into a little darkened membranous sac ( Figs. 58 A–B).

Female. Seventh abdominal sternite little more than twice as wide as long; apical margin roundly excised and provided with a distinct pit. Subgenital plate largely membranous with transverse riffles and two oval pits near base; apical area sclerotised; apical margin truncate at both sides with a little projecting central lobe with straight lateral margins and convex apical margin (
Fig. 59A
). Ovipositor elongate substraight with faintly approaching margins; tip with narrowed margins, subobtuse (
Fig. 59B
).
